com.interpss.dstab.controller.block

Interface ICMLFunctionExpression

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.hazelcast.nio.serialization.DataSerializable, ICMLBlock, ICMLFunctionBase
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CMLFunctionExpressionAdapter, GainExpFunction, GateValueExpFunction, HighValueExpFunction, LowValueExpFunction

    public interface ICMLFunctionExpression
extends ICMLFunctionBase
    We have two basic concepts: Block (StaticBlock and ControlBlock) and Function Block is two-way, which means you can find y from u and u(0) from y(0) Function is only way. You can only find y from a set of u(s). So function cannot put in the main path between RefPoint and Controller output This interface is design to represent function with a set of inputs, describing by expressions
